title: What songs has Bob Dylan written for other artists? - Quora

response.answer_text: Songs that he wrote and gave to other artists that he did not release first include: I’ll Keep It With Mine- recorded by Judy Collins and Nico Seven Days- Ronny Woods Mighty Quinn- Manfred Mann You Ain’t Goin Nowhere- The Byrds Too Much of Nothing - Peter, Paul and Mary Percy’s Song- Arlo Guthrie Tomorrow is Such a Long Time- Elvis Presley Wanted Man- Johnny Cash You Treat Me Like a Step Child - Solomon Burke When I Paint My Masterpiece and Blind Willie McTell - The Band more I am leaving out, I am sure.
I can give you 3 examples from the 60s but I'm sure there are many more:- Mr. Tambourine Man - The Byrds Mighty Quinn - Manfred Mann All Along The Watchtower - Jimi Hendrix.
